    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** providing our highest efficiency floor at 78.41; his matchup against Slade Cecconi is an ideal scenario for a power-heavy production day, bolstered by a significant order advantage batting second. **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** also present as elite starts (69.16 and 68.80, respectively) against Colin Rea. While Rea carries a 4.36 xERA, we are carefully monitoring the base-stealing potential for **Trea Turner**; despite his high score, the algorithm docked him 4% for facing a pitcher with a 63% hold rate. Similarly, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (61.34) and **Hyeseong Kim** (60.99) are strong plays, with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** specifically benefiting from a 14% boost due to dynamic platoon splits, even against a tough veteran like Aaron Nola.\n\nWe remain cautious regarding the lower end of our active roster, where the scarcity of stolen bases forces our hand. **Victor Scott II** (44.94) and **Kazuma Okamoto** (43.67) are marginal starts, but their presence is necessitated by the need to chase volume in our weakest category. **Dillon Dingler** is our most notable bench decision, failing to crack the starting lineup with a score of 36.01. Despite a favorable park factor, he was ultimately relegated to the bench because his 15% penalty for an unfavorable platoon split against Sonny Gray dropped his efficiency well below our required 40.0 floor. With **Christian Yelich**, **Zac Veen**, and **Lars Nootbaar** currently unavailable due to injury or roster status, we are operating with a tight rotation, leaning heavily on the consistency of **Junior Caminero** (57.44) and **Colt Keith** (51.46) to stabilize our offensive output against what are otherwise challenging matchups on the mound.",
